# Local Service Startup

When the user asks to start related/local services for this platform:

## Start
- MySQL (`:3306`), Redis (`:6379`) — usually already running locally
- Keycloak (`:8080`) via `keycloak/docker-compose.yaml` (Colima/Docker)
- Gateway (`:3001`) and Frontend (`:3000`)
- BuildingAI (`:4090` API / `:4091` UI) when AI Brain embed work needs it
- OpenCode (`:4096`) when code-factory work needs it — see **OpenCode local start** below
- **TaskView** — local dev: API `:1401`, web `:5174` (`pnpm dev:api` + `pnpm dev:webapp` in `../TaskView`); Docker alternate: web `:8888`, API `:1725`
- **Superset** — local non-Docker via `../superset/local_home/start-all.sh`: UI `localhost:9060` (iframe same-site with platform), API `127.0.0.1:9068`, Redis `:9063` (preferred). Docker `:8088` only if images already available. Gateway `subsystems.superset.baseUrl` must be `http://localhost:9060` — not `127.0.0.1`, or iframe SSO cookies will not stick.

## OpenCode local start (required)
Code Factory chat embeds OpenCode in an iframe at `http://localhost:4096`. If OpenCode is down, the UI shows “localhost 拒绝了我们的连接请求”.

**Always start without Basic Auth** so the iframe never pops a username/password dialog:
- Unset `OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD` and `OPENCODE_SERVER_USERNAME` (do not export them)
- Do **not** pass password-related flags; ignore `gateway/config.yaml` `subsystems.opencode.password` for local web bring-up
- Preferred command (binary usually at `~/.opencode/bin/opencode`):

```bash
unset OPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD OPENCODE_SERVER_USERNAME
opencode web --hostname 0.0.0.0 --port 4096 \
  --cors http://localhost:3000 --cors http://localhost:3001
```

- Verify: `curl -s -o /dev/null -w '%{http_code}\n' http://127.0.0.1:4096/` must return `200` **without** `-u`

## Do NOT start
- **DataEase** (`:8100`) — replaced by Superset; never start it as part of routine platform bring-up

## Notes
- Prefer updating/using `start-local.sh` to match this list
- Subsystem health probes that still mention DataEase are legacy; do not treat DataEase offline as a startup failure
- If TaskView/Superset/BuildingAI embed shows `platform-sso failed: 400`, Keycloak `gateway` client may be missing `profile`/`email` scopes (session username becomes Keycloak `sub` like `user-admin`). Fix with `bun gateway/scripts/fix-keycloak-gateway-scopes.ts`, then refresh (re-login optional; gateway now resolves sub→username).
- TaskView iframe auto-login: platform embeds `/?_tv=<view>&_embed=1&_t=&_r=`. Distinct `_tv` values (inbox/kanban/…) drive post-SSO routes; `_embed=1` hides TaskView’s own sidebar so platform nav is the only menu.
- TaskView API CORS must allow `http://localhost:5174` (and platform `:3000`). Without it, tokens are stored but `redirectToUser` fails with a CORS error and the login modal stays. Dev defaults live in `TaskView/api/src/middlewares/cors.ts`; also set `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` in `TaskView/api/.env`.
